Add 'secure' parameter to OAuthHandler constructor.When 'secure' is True, HTTPS will be used for OAuth requests being sent to Twitter.nThis only applies to the get token, authorize, and get access token requests. APInrequests will not use HTTPS unless the API object also has 'secure' set to True innits constructor.nnExample:nauth = OAuthHandler(token,secret,secure=True)  # use HTTPS for OAuth setupnnapi = API(auth)  #  will NOT use HTTPSnapi_https = API(auth, secure=True)  # will use HTTPS for API requests.nnSigned-off-by: Joshua <jroesslein@gmail.com>n

Fallback to using 'twitter.com' for OAuth.This fixes issue #8 for the time being until Twitter resolves thenissue on their end. See issue #1207 on the twitter API tracker.nnNote: API calls still use 'api.twitter.com', just the initial OAuthnsetup uses 'twitter.com'.n

Added ModelFactory. This replaces the 'models' dict in the tweepy.models module.This will allow for more flexible plug 'n play for developers that neednto extend Tweepy's models. To use custom models, they will extend the ModelFactorynand then pass this new factory into the API constructor.nnExample:nclass MyStatus(Status):nA extended Status modelnnclass MyModelFactory(ModelFactory):nstatus = MyStatusnnapi = API(model_factory=MyModelFactory)n

API.search() now includes search meta data as attributes of the ResultSet object returned.Example:nresults = api.search('python')nprint 'Search took %s seconds' % results.completed_innnThis fixes issue #10 (http://github.com/joshthecoder/tweepy/issues/#issue/10)nnMeta data available as of today:nmax_id, since_id, refresh_url, next_page, results_per_page,npage, completed_in, queryn

Refactored the way tweepy does parsing to make it more customizable by developers.All parsing of the response payload is now handled by a Parser class defined inntweepy/parsers.pynThe default parser used is ModelParser which parses a JSON payload into a model instance.nnDevelopers may define and use their own custom parsers by extending the Parser class.nTo use the custom parser:nnapi = API(parser=MyParser())n
